OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F419A1780570971
OL,3,CCouncil ad banned for 'misleading'
OL,4,Cdomestic fire pollution claim
OL,6,FAn ad by Brighton & Hove City Council
OL,7,Fhas been banned for misleadingly
OL,8,Fsuggesting a direct link between the
OL,9,Fuse of wood burners and open fires and
OL,10,Fan increase in pollution.
OL,12,FThe digital poster, seen in December,
OL,13,Fincluded a graphic of a wood-burning
OL,14,Fstove that was emitting smoke in the
OL,15,Fshape of an adult and child, and the
OL,16,Ftext: "Harmful particle pollution near
OL,17,F4 city primary schools was 78% higher
OL,18,Flast winter compared with last summer.
OL,19,FWood burners and open fires. The cosy
OL,20,Fkiller."
OL,26,@xD@GOU|D@HO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
